{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-06-09-2",
 "title": "Opening Night at Reckless Abandon",
 "summary": "On the first night of the swoop tournament at Corellia's Reckless Abandon Swoop Arena, three racers tear through a gauntlet of themed track sections -- ocean waves, Kashyyyk forest, Tibannopolis ravines, coral reefs, a lava-dragon volcano, Beggar's Canyon, Hoth's wampa tunnels, and the dianoga-infested sewers of Anoat. Joshua Arands of Team Corellia dominates the Grade 4 division aboard the Event Horizon, finishing well ahead despite a modest score, while Team KIF's Kestryan du Bracc braves the dianoga shortcut on the Repossessor and the disguised Bazil McKenzie, racing as Mege Vauki on the rookie LoanShark, plays it safe through the deadlier sections to crowd boos. All three survive the lethal course and post benchmark pace times for their grades, setting the bar for the rest of the tournament as the announcer thanks the event's sponsors.",
